    "code": "O26.00",
    "rawCode": "O2600",
    "shortDesc": "Excessive weight gain in pregnancy, unspecified trimester",
    "longDesc": "Excessive weight gain in pregnancy, unspecified trimester",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a pregnant person who is gaining weight too quickly during pregnancy, but the specific timing (first, second, or third trimester) is not specified. While some weight gain is normal and necessary during pregnancy to support the growing baby, excessive weight gain can increase risks like gestational diabetes, high blood pressure, and complications during delivery. The condition is identified when a healthcare provider determines the weight gain is beyond what's considered healthy for that particular pregnancy.",
    "whoUses": "Obstetricians and midwives use this code during prenatal care visits to track and monitor maternal weight gain throughout pregnancy. It commonly appears on prenatal care and obstetric billing statements and EOBs, and may trigger counseling about nutrition and safe exercise during pregnancy.",
